UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS - CHINA: GAS LEAK, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 30 Dec 2015
Source: Mashable.com [edited]
http://mashable.com/2015/11/30/shandong-gas-leak/#uy.kp1J0pSqo


A gas leak at a steel parts factory in eastern China has killed 10 people and left 7 others hospitalized with poisoning.

The Zouping County government said the leak at the Shandong Fukai Stainless Steel Company occurred at around 5:50 p.m. on Saturday [28 Nov 2015] and poisoned 17 people. Five of the victims died immediately, and 5 more died early Sunday [29 Nov 2015]. The other 7 remain in the hospital in stable condition.

The cause of the leak is under investigation. Satellite images show the factory next to warehouses and low-rise residential homes in a village about 60 km (40 miles) east of Jinan, the Shandong provincial capital.

According to local reports [link in Chinese], the municipal government set up an emergency meeting on Monday [30 Nov 2015] morning with 78 of the city's gas and energy companies to get them to be more vigilant against similar occurrences.

The deadly leak is the latest industrial accident in China, where authorities are under pressure to improve work safety after a huge chemical blast in Tianjin killed at least 140 people and left a swath of the port city in smoldering ruins.

[Byline: Victoria Ho]

