[Welding requires and produces a number of gasses. However, this article mentions "a gas leak," perhaps implying that it was not a gas produced in the welding process. This event could have been caused by natural gas for heating the welding facility. Workers may have not noticed a smell, assuming that the natural gas is treated to produce a smell for the purposes of sensing leaks. Either natural gas or fumes produced during the process of welding could potentially have terrible consequences.

We do not know whether the workers had any type of respiratory protection or whether there was any gas extraction apparatus in the welding plant.

Without more information, it is difficult to know to which gas or gasses the workers may have succumbed. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3830274,155.]

